{{Han etyl}}
{{liushu|p}} – a street intersection.

Originally symmetric, it has been simplified asymmetrically; the left half {{zh-l|*彳}} is widely used as a radical, while the right half {{zh-l|*亍}} finds occasional use, and the character can be broken up as {{Han compound|彳|亍}}, though originally it was not a compound.

